# .claudeignore — files Claude Code should not pull into context.
#
# NOTE: Claude Code does not (yet) natively enforce this file. It is honored as a
# shared convention and by some community PreToolUse hooks / other agents, and is
# here for forward-compatibility. The mechanisms that ARE enforced today:
#   - .gitignore (respected by the @ picker / discovery via respectGitignore)
#   - permissions.deny "Read(...)" rules in .claude/settings.json  <-- hard block
# Security-sensitive paths below are ALSO denied in .claude/settings.json so they
# are actually blocked, not just hinted.

# --- Dependencies & package manager noise ---
node_modules/
.npm/
*.lock
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml

# --- Build output / generated artifacts ---
bin/
obj/
dist/
build/
out/
artifacts/
[Dd]ebug/
[Rr]elease/
publish/
*.dll
*.exe
*.pdb
*.binlog

# --- Test / coverage output ---
TestResults/
coverage/
*.trx

# --- Logs & temp ---
*.log
logs/
*.tmp
*.cache
tmp/

# --- Secrets & credentials (ALSO hard-blocked via permissions.deny) ---
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key
*.pfx
*.p12
*.crt
secrets/
.secrets

# --- OS / IDE cruft ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# --- VCS internals ---
.git/

# --- AI tooling: local & generated (keep specs/design readable) ---
graphify-out/
.claude/settings.local.json
# Do NOT ignore: .specify/, DESIGN.md, CLAUDE.md — these are the
# source-of-truth context the workflow depends on.
